<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,898,1390]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1295,1319]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
As Pruthi did not dissect the male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[880,928,1295,1319]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">type</typeStatus>
specimens and the author was not allowed to dissect the same, no comment can be made on the relationships of the species. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pruthi, H. S." box="[1168,1337,1330,1354]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref74163" refString="Pruthi, H. S. (1930) Studies on Indian Jassidae (Homoptera). Part I. Introductory and description of some new genera and species. Memoirs of Indian Museum, 11, 1 - 68." type="journal article" year="1930">Pruthi’s (1930)</bibRefCitation>
description is quite adequate to distinguish the species based on the pronotal color.
</paragraph>
